        <div class="guidelinesColumns">
            <div fxFlex="660px">
                <p>If the text in tiles needs to be prominent enough to distinguish between primary content pieces, consider
                    using a different container, like a list or cards, optimized for displaying text and facilitating reading
                    comprehension.
                    <br />
                    <br />

                    <h4>Lists:</h4>
                    <p>Optimized for reading comprehension, particularly when comparing a set of data containing multiple data
                        types. </p>
                    <br />
                    <br />

                    <h4>Cards:</h4>
                    <p>Used for content with inconsistent formatting, such as photos with captions of variable length, or data
                        sets with heterogeneous content, such as a mixed collection of photos and videos and books.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

